            <title>[LUCENE-940] SimpleDateFormat used in a non thread safe manner</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-940</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;As Mike pointed out in &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mail-archive.com/java-dev@lucene.apache.org/msg10831.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;http://www.mail-archive.com/java-dev@lucene.apache.org/msg10831.html&lt;/a&gt; SimpleDateFormat is not thread safe and hence DocMakers need to maintain it in a ThreadLocal.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
